quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  29,1,"Alif-Lâm-Mîm."
  29,2,"Do people think that they will be left alone because they say: "We believe," and will not be tested."
  29,3,"And We indeed tested those who were before them. And Allâh will certainly make (it) known (the truth of) those who are true, and will certainly make (it) known (the falsehood of) those who are liars, (although Allâh knows all that before putting them to test)."
  29,4,"Or think those who do evil deeds that they can outstrip Us (i.e. escape Our punishment)? Evil is that which they judge!"
  29,5,"Whoever hopes for the Meeting{1} with Allâh, then Allâh’s Term is surely coming and He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower.",footnotes:1:1
  29,6,"And whosoever strives, he strives only for himself. Verily, Allâh stands not in need of any of the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, jinn, and all that exists)."